{
  "video_id": "NAkkckxE9i8",
  "title": "The unexpected beauty of everyday sounds | Meklit Hadero",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13309.0,
      "end_time": 15388.0,
      "text": "As a singer-songwriter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15412.0,
      "end_time": 19127.0,
      "text": "people often ask me about my influences or, as I like to call them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19151.0,
      "end_time": 21539.0,
      "text": "my sonic lineages."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21563.0,
      "end_time": 23191.0,
      "text": "And I could easily tell you"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23215.0,
      "end_time": 26634.0,
      "text": "that I was shaped by the jazz and hip hop that I grew up with,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26659.0,
      "end_time": 29970.0,
      "text": "by the Ethiopian heritage of my ancestors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29994.0,
      "end_time": 32897.0,
      "text": "or by the 1980s pop on my childhood radio stations."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33783.0,
      "end_time": 37374.0,
      "text": "But beyond genre, there is another question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 37398.0,
      "end_time": 42240.0,
      "text": "how do the sounds we hear every day influence the music that we make?"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42547.0,
      "end_time": 44599.0,
      "text": "I believe that everyday soundscape"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44624.0,
      "end_time": 48650.0,
      "text": "can be the most unexpected inspiration for songwriting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48890.0,
      "end_time": 50604.0,
      "text": "and to look at this idea a little bit more closely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 50628.0,
      "end_time": 52749.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to talk today about three things:"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 52773.0,
      "end_time": 55797.0,
      "text": "nature, language and silence --"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55821.0,
      "end_time": 59154.0,
      "text": "or rather, the impossibility of true silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 59827.0,
      "end_time": 62357.0,
      "text": "And through this I hope to give you a sense of a world"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 62381.0,
      "end_time": 65432.0,
      "text": "already alive with musical expression,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65456.0,
      "end_time": 69437.0,
      "text": "with each of us serving as active participants,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 69461.0,
      "end_time": 71716.0,
      "text": "whether we know it or not."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 72136.0,
      "end_time": 74954.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to start today with nature, but before we do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 74978.0,
      "end_time": 78250.0,
      "text": "let&#39;s quickly listen to this snippet of an opera singer warming up."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 78602.0,
      "end_time": 79758.0,
      "text": "Here it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80700.0,
      "end_time": 85700.0,
      "text": "(Singing)"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 95910.0,
      "end_time": 97600.0,
      "text": "(Singing ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 97571.0,
      "end_time": 99408.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s beautiful, isn&#39;t it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 100201.0,
      "end_time": 101351.0,
      "text": "Gotcha!"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 101376.0,
      "end_time": 104812.0,
      "text": "That is actually not the sound of an opera singer warming up."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 105161.0,
      "end_time": 107660.0,
      "text": "That is the sound of a bird"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 107684.0,
      "end_time": 109606.0,
      "text": "slowed down to a pace"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 109630.0,
      "end_time": 113351.0,
      "text": "that the human ear mistakenly recognizes as its own."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 114120.0,
      "end_time": 118816.0,
      "text": "It was released as part of Peter Szöke&#39;s 1987 Hungarian recording"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 118840.0,
      "end_time": 121222.0,
      "text": "\"The Unknown Music of Birds,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 121246.0,
      "end_time": 125116.0,
      "text": "where he records many birds and slows down their pitches"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 125141.0,
      "end_time": 126748.0,
      "text": "to reveal what&#39;s underneath."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 127615.0,
      "end_time": 129644.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s listen to the full-speed recording."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 131650.0,
      "end_time": 135110.0,
      "text": "(Bird singing)"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 135638.0,
      "end_time": 137550.0,
      "text": "Now, let&#39;s hear the two of them together"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 137574.0,
      "end_time": 139146.0,
      "text": "so your brain can juxtapose them."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 140167.0,
      "end_time": 145167.0,
      "text": "(Bird singing at slow then full speed)"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 158338.0,
      "end_time": 160338.0,
      "text": "(Singing ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 162630.0,
      "end_time": 163254.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s incredible."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 163864.0,
      "end_time": 168126.0,
      "text": "Perhaps the techniques of opera singing were inspired by birdsong."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 168880.0,
      "end_time": 173768.0,
      "text": "As humans, we intuitively understand birds to be our musical teachers."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 174439.0,
      "end_time": 177343.0,
      "text": "In Ethiopia, birds are considered an integral part"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 177367.0,
      "end_time": 179972.0,
      "text": "of the origin of music itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 180542.0,
      "end_time": 182170.0,
      "text": "The story goes like this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 183538.0,
      "end_time": 188571.0,
      "text": "1,500 years ago, a young man was born in the Empire of Aksum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 188595.0,
      "end_time": 191142.0,
      "text": "a major trading center of the ancient world."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 191525.0,
      "end_time": 193660.0,
      "text": "His name was Yared."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 194402.0,
      "end_time": 197609.0,
      "text": "When Yared was seven years old his father died,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 197634.0,
      "end_time": 201256.0,
      "text": "and his mother sent him to go live with an uncle, who was a priest"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 201281.0,
      "end_time": 203576.0,
      "text": "of the Ethiopian Orthodox tradition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 203600.0,
      "end_time": 205733.0,
      "text": "one of the oldest churches in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 206892.0,
      "end_time": 210353.0,
      "text": "Now, this tradition has an enormous amount of scholarship and learning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 210377.0,
      "end_time": 213389.0,
      "text": "and Yared had to study and study and study and study,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 213413.0,
      "end_time": 216290.0,
      "text": "and one day he was studying under a tree,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 216530.0,
      "end_time": 218579.0,
      "text": "when three birds came to him."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 219321.0,
      "end_time": 222389.0,
      "text": "One by one, these birds became his teachers."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 222912.0,
      "end_time": 226204.0,
      "text": "They taught him music -- scales, in fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 227579.0,
      "end_time": 230820.0,
      "text": "And Yared, eventually recognized as Saint Yared,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 230106.0,
      "end_time": 234543.0,
      "text": "used these scales to compose five volumes of chants and hymns"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 234568.0,
      "end_time": 236740.0,
      "text": "for worship and celebration."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 236764.0,
      "end_time": 240153.0,
      "text": "And he used these scales to compose and to create"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 240177.0,
      "end_time": 242927.0,
      "text": "an indigenous musical notation system."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 243645.0,
      "end_time": 247268.0,
      "text": "And these scales evolved into what is known as kiñit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 247292.0,
      "end_time": 253185.0,
      "text": "the unique, pentatonic, five-note, modal system that is very much alive"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 253209.0,
      "end_time": 257433.0,
      "text": "and thriving and still evolving in Ethiopia today."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 258531.0,
      "end_time": 261694.0,
      "text": "Now, I love this story because it&#39;s true at multiple levels."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 261718.00000000003,
      "end_time": 264741.0,
      "text": "Saint Yared was a real, historical figure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 264765.0,
      "end_time": 268714.0,
      "text": "and the natural world can be our musical teacher."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 269570.0,
      "end_time": 271211.0,
      "text": "And we have so many examples of this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 271235.0,
      "end_time": 273458.0,
      "text": "the Pygmies of the Congo tune their instruments"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 273482.0,
      "end_time": 276820.0,
      "text": "to the pitches of the birds in the forest around them."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 276396.0,
      "end_time": 279574.0,
      "text": "Musician and natural soundscape expert Bernie Krause describes"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 279598.0,
      "end_time": 282972.0,
      "text": "how a healthy environment has animals and insects"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 282996.0,
      "end_time": 286424.0,
      "text": "taking up low, medium and high-frequency bands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 286448.0,
      "end_time": 289642.0,
      "text": "in exactly the same way as a symphony does."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 290660.0,
      "end_time": 294429.0,
      "text": "And countless works of music were inspired by bird and forest song."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 294972.0,
      "end_time": 299844.0,
      "text": "Yes, the natural world can be our cultural teacher."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 300751.0,
      "end_time": 304123.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s go now to the uniquely human world of language."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 305830.0,
      "end_time": 308327.0,
      "text": "Every language communicates with pitch to varying degrees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 308351.0,
      "end_time": 309789.0,
      "text": "whether it&#39;s Mandarin Chinese,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 309813.0,
      "end_time": 313805.0,
      "text": "where a shift in melodic inflection gives the same phonetic syllable"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 313829.0,
      "end_time": 315586.0,
      "text": "an entirely different meaning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 315610.0,
      "end_time": 316952.0,
      "text": "to a language like English,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 316976.0,
      "end_time": 319346.0,
      "text": "where a raised pitch at the end of a sentence ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 319370.0,
      "end_time": 321388.0,
      "text": "(Going up in pitch) implies a question?"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 321412.0,
      "end_time": 323200.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 323450.0,
      "end_time": 324704.0,
      "text": "As an Ethiopian-American woman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 324728.0,
      "end_time": 327136.0,
      "text": "I grew up around the language of Amharic, Amhariña."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 327160.0,
      "end_time": 329639.0,
      "text": "It was my first language, the language of my parents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 329663.0,
      "end_time": 332220.0,
      "text": "one of the main languages of Ethiopia."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 332716.0,
      "end_time": 335910.0,
      "text": "And there are a million reasons to fall in love with this language:"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 335934.0,
      "end_time": 338775.0,
      "text": "its depth of poetics, its double entendres,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 338799.0,
      "end_time": 341416.0,
      "text": "its wax and gold, its humor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 341440.0,
      "end_time": 345330.0,
      "text": "its proverbs that illuminate the wisdom and follies of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 346380.0,
      "end_time": 350117.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s also this melodicism, a musicality built right in."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 350734.0,
      "end_time": 352609.0,
      "text": "And I find this distilled most clearly"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 352633.0,
      "end_time": 355106.0,
      "text": "in what I like to call emphatic language --"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 355130.0,
      "end_time": 357366.0,
      "text": "language that&#39;s meant to highlight or underline"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 357390.0,
      "end_time": 359445.0,
      "text": "or that springs from surprise."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 360360.0,
      "end_time": 362443.0,
      "text": "Take, for example, the word: \"indey.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 363204.0,
      "end_time": 365306.0,
      "text": "Now, if there are Ethiopians in the audience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 365330.0,
      "end_time": 367337.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re probably chuckling to themselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 367361.0,
      "end_time": 369445.0,
      "text": "because the word means something like \"No!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 369469.0,
      "end_time": 371280.0,
      "text": "or \"How could he?\" or \"No, he didn&#39;t.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 371304.0,
      "end_time": 373405.0,
      "text": "It kind of depends on the situation."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 373429.0,
      "end_time": 377280.0,
      "text": "But when I was a kid, this was my very favorite word,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 377304.0,
      "end_time": 380404.0,
      "text": "and I think it&#39;s because it has a pitch."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 380721.0,
      "end_time": 381932.0,
      "text": "It has a melody."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 381956.0,
      "end_time": 384957.0,
      "text": "You can almost see the shape as it springs from someone&#39;s mouth."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 384981.0,
      "end_time": 387710.0,
      "text": "\"Indey\" -- it dips, and then raises again."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 388391.0,
      "end_time": 391480.0,
      "text": "And as a musician and composer, when I hear that word,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 391504.0,
      "end_time": 394573.0,
      "text": "something like this is floating through my mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 395982.0,
      "end_time": 400982.0,
      "text": "(Music and singing \"Indey\")"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 405832.0,
      "end_time": 407832.0,
      "text": "(Music ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 408711.0,
      "end_time": 412702.0,
      "text": "Or take, for example, the phrase for \"It is right\" or \"It is correct\" --"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 412726.0,
      "end_time": 414298.0,
      "text": "\"Lickih nehu ... Lickih nehu.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 414322.0,
      "end_time": 416955.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an affirmation, an agreement."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 416979.0,
      "end_time": 418137.0,
      "text": "\"Lickih nehu.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 418161.0,
      "end_time": 419313.0,
      "text": "When I hear that phrase,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 419337.0,
      "end_time": 422834.0,
      "text": "something like this starts rolling through my mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 424310.0,
      "end_time": 429310.0,
      "text": "(Music and singing \"Lickih nehu\")"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 431572.0,
      "end_time": 433572.0,
      "text": "(Music ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 434199.0,
      "end_time": 437160.0,
      "text": "And in both of those cases, what I did was I took the melody"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 437400.0,
      "end_time": 439499.0,
      "text": "and the phrasing of those words and phrases"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 439523.0,
      "end_time": 444890.0,
      "text": "and I turned them into musical parts to use in these short compositions."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 444539.0,
      "end_time": 446200.0,
      "text": "And I like to write bass lines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 446440.0,
      "end_time": 448940.0,
      "text": "so they both ended up kind of as bass lines."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 449387.0,
      "end_time": 452130.0,
      "text": "Now, this is based on the work of Jason Moran and others"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 452370.0,
      "end_time": 455750.0,
      "text": "who work intimately with music and language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 455990.0,
      "end_time": 458430.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s also something I&#39;ve had in my head since I was a kid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 458670.0,
      "end_time": 460980.0,
      "text": "how musical my parents sounded"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 460122.0,
      "end_time": 463274.0,
      "text": "when they were speaking to each other and to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 464700.0,
      "end_time": 466444.0,
      "text": "It was from them and from Amhariña that I learned"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 466468.0,
      "end_time": 469348.0,
      "text": "that we are awash in musical expression"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 469372.0,
      "end_time": 471987.0,
      "text": "with every word, every sentence that we speak,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 472110.0,
      "end_time": 474763.0,
      "text": "every word, every sentence that we receive."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 474787.0,
      "end_time": 479460.0,
      "text": "Perhaps you can hear it in the words I&#39;m speaking even now."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 480237.0,
      "end_time": 482652.0,
      "text": "Finally, we go to the 1950s United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 482676.0,
      "end_time": 486587.0,
      "text": "and the most seminal work of 20th century avant-garde composition:"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 486611.0,
      "end_time": 488735.0,
      "text": "John Cage&#39;s \"4:33,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 488759.0,
      "end_time": 491993.0,
      "text": "written for any instrument or combination of instruments."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 492912.0,
      "end_time": 496471.0,
      "text": "The musician or musicians are invited to walk onto the stage"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 496495.0,
      "end_time": 499685.0,
      "text": "with a stopwatch and open the score,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 499709.0,
      "end_time": 502640.0,
      "text": "which was actually purchased by the Museum of Modern Art --"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 502664.0,
      "end_time": 504460.0,
      "text": "the score, that is."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 504641.0,
      "end_time": 508149.0,
      "text": "And this score has not a single note written"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 508173.0,
      "end_time": 510647.0,
      "text": "and there is not a single note played"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 510671.0,
      "end_time": 513403.0,
      "text": "for four minutes and 33 seconds."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 514539.0,
      "end_time": 519230.0,
      "text": "And, at once enraging and enrapturing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 519254.0,
      "end_time": 522142.0,
      "text": "Cage shows us that even when there are no strings"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 522166.00000000006,
      "end_time": 527214.0,
      "text": "being plucked by fingers or hands hammering piano keys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 527238.0,
      "end_time": 529715.0,
      "text": "still there is music, still there is music,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 529739.0,
      "end_time": 531801.0,
      "text": "still there is music."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 531825.0,
      "end_time": 533953.0,
      "text": "And what is this music?"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 534903.0,
      "end_time": 537108.0,
      "text": "It was that sneeze in the back."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 537132.0,
      "end_time": 538678.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 538702.0,
      "end_time": 543762.0,
      "text": "It is the everyday soundscape that arises from the audience themselves:"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 543787.0,
      "end_time": 548560.0,
      "text": "their coughs, their sighs, their rustles, their whispers, their sneezes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 548800.0,
      "end_time": 550621.0,
      "text": "the room, the wood of the floors and the walls"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 550645.0,
      "end_time": 553103.0,
      "text": "expanding and contracting, creaking and groaning"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 553127.0,
      "end_time": 554531.0,
      "text": "with the heat and the cold,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 554555.0,
      "end_time": 557646.0,
      "text": "the pipes clanking and contributing."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 559306.0,
      "end_time": 562946.0,
      "text": "And controversial though it was, and even controversial though it remains,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 562970.0,
      "end_time": 567214.0,
      "text": "Cage&#39;s point is that there is no such thing as true silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 568107.0,
      "end_time": 572612.0,
      "text": "Even in the most silent environments, we still hear and feel the sound"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 572636.0,
      "end_time": 574163.0,
      "text": "of our own heartbeats."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 574646.0,
      "end_time": 577814.0,
      "text": "The world is alive with musical expression."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 578383.0,
      "end_time": 580590.0,
      "text": "We are already immersed."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 582330.0,
      "end_time": 586230.0,
      "text": "Now, I had my own moment of, let&#39;s say, remixing John Cage"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 586470.0,
      "end_time": 587714.0,
      "text": "a couple of months ago"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 587738.0,
      "end_time": 590741.0,
      "text": "when I was standing in front of the stove cooking lentils."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 590765.0,
      "end_time": 593907.0,
      "text": "And it was late one night and it was time to stir,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 593931.0,
      "end_time": 595903.0,
      "text": "so I lifted the lid off the cooking pot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 595927.0,
      "end_time": 598360.0,
      "text": "and I placed it onto the kitchen counter next to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 598384.0,
      "end_time": 600647.0,
      "text": "and it started to roll back and forth"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 600671.0,
      "end_time": 603432.0,
      "text": "making this sound."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 604765.0,
      "end_time": 609765.0,
      "text": "(Sound of metal lid clanking against a counter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 610929.0,
      "end_time": 612790.0,
      "text": "(Clanking ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 613525.0,
      "end_time": 615590.0,
      "text": "And it stopped me cold."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 615727.0,
      "end_time": 620949.0,
      "text": "I thought, \"What a weird, cool swing that cooking pan lid has.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 622200.0,
      "end_time": 626784.0,
      "text": "So when the lentils were ready and eaten,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 626808.0,
      "end_time": 630302.0,
      "text": "I hightailed it to my backyard studio,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 630326.0,
      "end_time": 632169.0,
      "text": "and I made this."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 633187.0,
      "end_time": 638187.0,
      "text": "(Music, including the sound of the lid, and singing)"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 650271.0,
      "end_time": 651420.0,
      "text": "(Music ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 652479.0,
      "end_time": 654891.0,
      "text": "Now, John Cage wasn&#39;t instructing musicians"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 654915.0,
      "end_time": 658610.0,
      "text": "to mine the soundscape for sonic textures to turn into music."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 659600.0,
      "end_time": 661912.0,
      "text": "He was saying that on its own,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 661937.0,
      "end_time": 665398.0,
      "text": "the environment is musically generative,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 665422.0,
      "end_time": 669663.0,
      "text": "that it is generous, that it is fertile,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 669687.0,
      "end_time": 671850.0,
      "text": "that we are already immersed."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 672765.0,
      "end_time": 678778.0,
      "text": "Musician, music researcher, surgeon and human hearing expert Charles Limb"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 678802.0,
      "end_time": 680857.0,
      "text": "is a professor at Johns Hopkins University"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 680881.0,
      "end_time": 683150.0,
      "text": "and he studies music and the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 684739.0,
      "end_time": 686505.0,
      "text": "And he has a theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 687735.0,
      "end_time": 690831.0,
      "text": "that it is possible -- it is possible --"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 690855.0,
      "end_time": 696300.0,
      "text": "that the human auditory system actually evolved to hear music,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 696270.0,
      "end_time": 701980.0,
      "text": "because it is so much more complex than it needs to be for language alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 701733.0,
      "end_time": 703507.0,
      "text": "And if that&#39;s true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 703532.0,
      "end_time": 706477.0,
      "text": "it means that we&#39;re hard-wired for music,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 706501.0,
      "end_time": 708614.0,
      "text": "that we can find it anywhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 708638.0,
      "end_time": 711716.0,
      "text": "that there is no such thing as a musical desert,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 711740.0,
      "end_time": 715439.0,
      "text": "that we are permanently hanging out at the oasis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 715463.0,
      "end_time": 717520.0,
      "text": "and that is marvelous."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 718135.0,
      "end_time": 721328.0,
      "text": "We can add to the soundtrack, but it&#39;s already playing."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 722260.0,
      "end_time": 724114.0,
      "text": "And it doesn&#39;t mean don&#39;t study music."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 724138.0,
      "end_time": 728634.0,
      "text": "Study music, trace your sonic lineages and enjoy that exploration."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 729355.0,
      "end_time": 733900.0,
      "text": "But there is a kind of sonic lineage to which we all belong."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 734267.0,
      "end_time": 736890.0,
      "text": "So the next time you are seeking percussion inspiration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 736914.0,
      "end_time": 740263.0,
      "text": "look no further than your tires, as they roll over the unusual grooves"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 740287.0,
      "end_time": 742110.0,
      "text": "of the freeway,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 742350.0,
      "end_time": 744213.0,
      "text": "or the top-right burner of your stove"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 744237.0,
      "end_time": 745945.0,
      "text": "and that strange way that it clicks"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 745970.0,
      "end_time": 748320.0,
      "text": "as it is preparing to light."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 748733.0,
      "end_time": 750344.0,
      "text": "When seeking melodic inspiration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 750369.0,
      "end_time": 753861.0,
      "text": "look no further than dawn and dusk avian orchestras"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 753885.0,
      "end_time": 757113.0,
      "text": "or to the natural lilt of emphatic language."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 757137.0,
      "end_time": 760136.0,
      "text": "We are the audience and we are the composers"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 760160.0,
      "end_time": 761954.0,
      "text": "and we take from these pieces"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 761979.0,
      "end_time": 763130.0,
      "text": "we are given."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 763154.0,
      "end_time": 765220.0,
      "text": "We make, we make, we make, we make,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 765460.0,
      "end_time": 769466.0,
      "text": "knowing that when it comes to nature or language or soundscape,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 769490.0,
      "end_time": 772487.0,
      "text": "there is no end to the inspiration --"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 772511.0,
      "end_time": 774944.0,
      "text": "if we are listening."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 775421.0,
      "end_time": 776573.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 776597.0,
      "end_time": 782371.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}